cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about text style transfer, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper proposes a new model that leverages linguistic information to preserve the content during style transfer, which involves deep learning techniques. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. The paper also uses language models and performs experiments to evaluate the proposed model, which are related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the task of sentiment and political slant transfer, which involves text classification and image processing techniques, respectively. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a possible category.
